# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — CLAUDE.md

## Stack
- WordPress via Bedrock (composer-managed), theme: Sage 11 (Acorn 6, Blade, Vite).
- PHP {{PHP_VERSION}} (>=8.3). DB: {{DB_ENGINE}}.

## Model & agents
- All subagents use Opus 4.8 (`claude-opus-4-8`). This local instruction overrides defaults.
- Roles: wp-analyst, wp-architect, wp-engineer, wp-security-reviewer, wp-tester.

## TWO-LANE INVARIANT (NEVER VIOLATE)
- CODE goes UP: git/deploy push code only.
- CONTENT/DB goes DOWN: pull DB from production to local only.
- Deploy NEVER pushes the database upstream. Never commit DB dumps or .env.
- This rule is enforced by guard-two-lane.sh (PreToolUse, fail-closed), NOT by permission globs.

## Quality gates (must pass before "done")
- PHPCS (WPCS) clean (fast, runs on every edit), PHPStan green (runs at gate, not per-edit),
  PHPUnit green, Playwright E2E green.
- Security: zero critical findings on the diff.

## Client self-editing
- Editable regions use templateLock/contentOnly; client roles are restricted (see mu-plugins/claudepress-roles.php).

## Content & preview seeding
- You MAY populate the DEV database with PLACEHOLDER content for preview via WP-CLI / the WordPress MCP
  (`wp post create`, `wp option update`, `wp wc product create`). The two-lane guard does NOT block content CRUD.
- To promote placeholders to staging, author them as the idempotent seeder `web/app/mu-plugins/content-seed.php`:
  `wp claudepress seed` runs on dev/staging ONLY (never production), is create-if-absent, so a client's later edits
  are never overwritten. NEVER push the raw DB upstream.

## Deploy
- Deploy = git push to a branch your host watches (host-agnostic: Coolify / own VPS / Forge / GitHub Actions).
- Staging: `/claudepress:deploy-staging` (runs gates, pushes the staging branch). CODE only — DB/content/orders are NEVER deployed.
- Production stays HUMAN-GATED: never auto-deploy to prod; the prod deploy trigger is denied.

## Request intake
- When the user RELAYS a client/customer request ("the client wants…", "zákazník chce…"),
  the `intake` skill auto-triages it → right-sizes the process → (for non-trivial) writes a
  spec to `.claude/requests/` (git-ignored, PII) → asks for approval → hands off to wp-orchestrator.
- Pure content requests are routed to client self-edit / the seeder, not the dev pipeline.
- Checkout/payment/order requests force a human gate + security sign-off.

## Effort tuning (override here if desired)
- wp-engineer runs at effort: high (most consequential, multi-file). wp-tester at medium.
  Adjust per machine/budget in this file.

